title: EPC boys soccer all-stars announced; Whitehall's Javaughn Hussett is MVP
text:
By Kyle Craig | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 19, 2015 4:47 PM, updated October 19, 2015 5:02 PM View/Post Comments 
The Eastern Pennsylvania Conference boys soccer coaches have selected their 2015 all-stars. 
Whitehall senior forward Javaughn Hussett was named the conference’s Most Valuable Player. He has scored 15 goals this year for the Zephyrs. 
Liberty and Emmaus each had three representatives on the EPC first team. 
Here’s the complete list of all-conference teams, as selected by the coaches:
